I’m kind of overwhelmed with emotion posting this. If you don’t know I struggle with anxiety and depression and felt lost after stopping dance and then changing from engineering to art major. But it’s been the wildest time of my life and I’m so thankful to the friends I’ve made this year and I really can’t help but cry. This year reminded me why I chose to live and why I keep going. It’s been so crazy in my home life and personal life in ways I can’t express but the joy that my friends and costumes give to me has been so much. 
I wake up and look forward to just breathing, and looking at things l, and I cry over sunrises. It’s been such a blast. Not to mention even though I created less cosplays this year I was dressing up every other weekend for work or for cosplay guesting or hanging out with friends and it was amazing. Anyways cheers to freaking evolving and working on yourself. 
.

Do you think cosplay is hard? Or does it depend on the skill level or style of cosplay? To me honestly I feel like all cosplay is difficult. Doesn’t matter what kind of cosplay you do. Even those who just do makeup sometimes have to test and redo their makeup for hours and hours. Even those who do cosplay for fun often spend hours of time making sure the cosplay is a perfect fit, the perfect color, the perfect texture. No one is more meticulous then cosplayers who do this full time honestly. They have a vision and dedication to it that I personally do not and I admire them for it. Hopping to be a less of a perfectionist this year so that I can actually go out and enjoy the things I made!! 
Also the majority of this is me prepping for katsucon so 😩 I really gotta be putting in the crazy hours to make everything on time.

What shoes do you wear? Also after allot of DMs I’ve decided to post a video on how I paint my shoes for cosplay. 
Firstly I wipe off my shoes to have a clean surface to paint on, then use blue painters tape to section off the areas I don’t want to paint l, if you paint the bottom of your shoes your shoes get really slippery and they’re harder to walk in, don’t paint your zipper either, you gotta zip it up after wards! When you paint I make sure to paint in thin coats especially with leather paint since a little goes a crazy long way. With fast drying leather paint wait 25-30 minutes in between coats. That’s about an episode of gargoyles. Then once you reach your desired coat shade amount seal it with either a flexible gloss or a flexible mate gloss I specifically have one for shoes but flex bond or modge podge is a good alternative. 
In the style of my favorite Forager happy crafting don’t cry! 
.

Have any funny embarrassing moments? 🤣

Oh my goodness it was so funny recording outside with @cosplaychoco 🤣 We didn’t think any trucks or cars could drive through this wild weather but it turns out they really won’t let a ton of snow stop them. It took us like 15 minutes to stop laughing at the situation. Can you tell that we don’t cosplay around normal people often? 

Also, yes we were cold but it’s so fun being in the snow. We both didn’t grow up with it so it just seems so magical. It’s also so fun to play in! Also, it reminded us of Dragonspine in Genshin since it’s a cold mountain 🤣 We had to go inside a couple time to warm up our hands but it was worth it to have fun with my bestie! Also, no one better talk about how we’re wearing the wrong shoes. We chose safety and comfort over aesthetics… for once.

Wish me luck during this snow storm cause it hasn’t really stopped. Heated blankets are keeping me comfy right now.

I can’t believe I went to cosplay to costume designer. in a blink of an eye and I haven’t even finished school yet 😭 but I got the chance to design from @blacktheatretroupe showing of August Wilson’s Joe Turner’s come and gone. August Wilson was seen as the theater poet of black America and to have my first show be with a black theater troupe, with showing starting on the first weekend of black history month, with a black cast it was the most fulfilling thing I’ve ever done. I’m very thankful for the opportunity! 
Also it’s extremely rare to be able to take part in an an August Wilson play since he’s a revered part of black theater history. His plays are also heavily protected and respected so it was nice to be able to see this play come to life with a little trace of my own creativity. Thank you to all my friends that supported me through this! 
.
#theater #28daysofblackcosplay #blackhistorymonth #blackgirlmagic #cosplay #crafting #sewing #artistsoninstagram #blackartist #buyblack #arizona #edwardian #historical

Cleaning up a little bit in the new year! One of my goals this year is to be more organized. As a crafter that has a habit of keeping every significant scrap that I can find, sorting out my supplies can be a hassle but it’s so good in the long run knowing all of the trims that you have and just have it easy and accessible to find. I personally love the rectangle card board method for trims because I find it was easier to store in boxes and cabinets. It’s also a blessing when your 20 yards of cording isn’t a hot mess anymore!! 😭 I’m not the first person to use it but I figured I would share!!
